# Postgres Control Tower — Project Rules

This is the authoritative summary of decisions in `PLAN.md`. When generic
best-practices conflict with anything here, **this file wins**. If `PLAN.md`
changes, update this file too.

## What we are building

A centralized control plane for fleets of PostgreSQL clusters managed with
pgBackRest, plus a unified multi-source log collector (PostgreSQL, pgBackRest,
Patroni, etcd, OS/journald). Three deployable units in v1: **manager image**,
**agent image**, **postgres**. Nothing else.

## Locked tech stack (do not introduce alternatives)

- **Backend (manager + agent):** Python 3.12, FastAPI, SQLAlchemy 2.x,
  Alembic, Pydantic v2, APScheduler, httpx, uvicorn.
- **DB:** PostgreSQL 16, single instance. Native partitioning for `logs.events`.
  Two schemas: `pct` (metadata) and `logs` (high volume).
- **Frontend:** React 18, Vite, TypeScript, TailwindCSS, shadcn/ui (dark mode
  default), TanStack Query, Recharts.
- **Auth:** UI uses JWT (HS256, manager-issued). Agents use a Bearer token
  issued at registration and **stored hashed** at rest.
- **Packaging:** `pip` + `pyproject.toml`. Multi-stage Dockerfiles. Docker
  Compose for the demo.

## Explicitly excluded from v1 (do not suggest, do not add)

- **No Redis, no Celery.** Background work is APScheduler in the manager plus
  a `pct.jobs` table that agents long-poll.
- **No Loki, no Vector.** Logs land in `logs.events` in the same Postgres,
  partitioned monthly.
- **No Nginx.** Uvicorn is fine for the prototype.
- **No mTLS / no PKI.** v1 is HTTPS + per-agent pre-shared bearer token.
  mTLS, RBAC roles beyond viewer/admin, and confirmation modals belong in
  `docs/hardening.md` as the v2 path.
- **No Next.js, no SSR, no App Router.** Plain Vite + React, served as
  static assets by the manager FastAPI process.
- **No Go.** Python end-to-end.
- **Out of scope for v1:** PITR restore UI, stanza-delete, config push & drift
  detection, "type cluster name to confirm" modals, PagerDuty/Teams notifiers,
  multi-tenant, S3 log archival.

## Communication model (don't break this)

- Agents always initiate. DB hosts need **no inbound ports**.
- Endpoints (versioned under `/api/v1`):
  - `POST /agents/register` — initial enrollment with shared token.
  - `POST /agents/heartbeat` — status + WAL health snapshot + `clock_skew_ms`.
  - `POST /logs/ingest` — batched, UTC-normalized log records.
  - `GET  /jobs/next` — long-poll for pending jobs.
  - `POST /jobs/{id}/result` — return job stdout/exit code.
- UTC normalization happens **at the agent**, using host TZ + NTP-reported
  skew. Always ship `clock_skew_ms` with each heartbeat.

## Job kinds — allowlist (defense in depth)

Allowed in v1, enforced in **both** manager API and agent runner:

- `backup_full`, `backup_diff`, `backup_incr`
- `check`
- `stanza_create`

`restore`, `stanza_delete`, and any other destructive op are **blocked at the
agent level**, not just hidden in the UI. Do not add them to the agent runner
under any circumstances in v1.

## Data model anchors

- Schema `pct`: `clusters`, `agents`, `pgbackrest_info`, `wal_health`, `jobs`,
  `alerts`, `users`.
- Schema `logs`: `logs.events` (partitioned monthly, btree on
  `(agent_id, ts_utc)`, GIN on `parsed`), `logs.role_transitions`.
- `users.role` is one of `viewer` | `admin` only.
- `agents.role` is one of `primary` | `replica` | `unknown`.
- `clusters.kind` is one of `standalone` | `patroni`.

## Repo layout

```
manager/pct_manager/        FastAPI app + scheduler + ingest + alerter
manager/alembic/            migrations
agent/pct_agent/            collectors/, runner.py, shipper.py
web/                        Vite + React + Tailwind + shadcn/ui
docs/                       all documentation
deploy/docker/              Dockerfiles
deploy/compose/             docker-compose.yml + patroni configs + seeds
deploy/scripts/             bootstrap.sh, teardown.sh, demo-failures.sh
PLAN.md                     authoritative implementation plan
```

## Configuration

All env vars are prefixed `PCT_`. See `.env.example`. Never read unprefixed
env vars in app code; always go through the settings module.

## Phase awareness

Work follows the P1–P9 checklist in `PLAN.md`. Don't introduce code for a
later phase while an earlier one is incomplete unless explicitly asked. When
in doubt about whether something belongs in v1 or v2, default to v1 minimum
viable and document the v2 idea in `docs/hardening.md` or
`docs/conflicts-resolved.md`.
